            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monitoring and Scaling Strategies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement comprehensive monitoring using tools like Prometheus and Grafana to track API metrics such as request rate, error rate, and inference time. Set up auto-scaling rules based on CPU/GPU utilization to handle traffic spikes. Use distributed tracing to identify bottlenecks in the inference pipeline, and log key events for auditability."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Common Operational Challenges"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Address issues like model drift by periodically retraining and redeploying the BGE M3 model. For API errors, implement circuit breakers to isolate failures and use fallback mechanisms. Ensure data privacy by encrypting requests and responses, and validate input schemas to prevent malformed data from causing crashes."
          }
        ]
